The new species can be recognized by the following combination of characters: (
1
) the size of the body (
13­20 mm
long, 
0.5–0.7 mm
wide, segment number (
38
)– 
40–56
); (
2
) the form of spermatheca, with 
9–10
large, sessile, globular diverticula, long and thick ectal ducts, and two very large (
80–130
μm long) eggshaped ectal glands; (
3
) maximum ten chaetae per bundle; (
4
) all pairs of pharyngeal glands with ventral lobes and the dorsal connection absent; (
5
) the clitellum is girdle shaped, hyalocytes and granulocytes arrangement reticulate; (
6
) seminal vesicle is large; (
7
) penial slit is longitudinal with more transverse components; and (
9
) three subneural glands in XIV–XVI.
